<h2 id="how-to-add-new-categories">How to add new categories</h2>

<h3 id="quick-method">Quick method</h3>

<p>At the quick category creator, add the name of the category, hit <strong>enter</strong> on your keyboard and, when you are done, press the â€˜<strong>Sendâ€™</strong>Â button as explained in the following screenshot.</p>

<p><a href="//docs.yclas.com/images/quick-category.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//docs.yclas.com/images/quick-category.png" alt="How to add categories and manage them 1" />
</a></p>

<h3 id="manual-method">Manual method</h3>

<p>1. Go to <strong>Panel</strong> - choose <strong>Classifieds</strong> &gt; <strong>Categories</strong></p>

<p>2. Press â€˜<strong>New category</strong>â€™ button</p>

<p>3. <strong>Fill in the fields:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Name:</strong> Choose a name for the category that will be displayed in a listing, e.g. â€œJobsâ€, â€œApartmentsâ€. Basically, this field is the most important, the rest are kind of optional.</li>
  <li><strong>Order:</strong> You can choose the order in which the subcategories will be displayed within a parent category. Itâ€™s not obligatory - later you can just use â€œdrag &amp; dropâ€ to change the order.</li>
  <li><strong>Parent:</strong> Here you can choose and create main and sub categories. If you choose â€œHome Categoryâ€, that category will become the main one. If a category is choosen as â€œParentâ€, everything within that category is a subcategory.</li>
  <li><strong>Seoname:</strong> A seoname will be auto-generated based on the name of category, but you can change it if you want it to be different.</li>
  <li><strong>Description:</strong> You can add a few words about what is available in this category.</li>
  <li><strong>Price:</strong> If you want people to pay for posting in this category, set your price here. Leave blank if itâ€™s free to post.</li>
</ul>

<p>4. Press <strong>SUBMIT</strong></p>

<p><a href="//docs.yclas.com/images/new-category.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//docs.yclas.com/images/new-category.png" alt="How to add categories and manage them 1" />
</a></p>

<p>After submitting, you should receive this message:</p>

<p>â€œ<em>Success. Item created. Please, to see the changes, delete the cacheâ€</em>.</p>

<p>Continue creating new categories if necessary, but remember to <strong>delete cache</strong> after finishing to see the changes. To delete cache, go to: <strong>Tools</strong> &gt; <strong>Cache</strong> on the left sidebar and press â€˜<strong>Delete all</strong>â€™. You can visit the site to see the changes youâ€™ve made.</p>

<p>While adding categories, you should remember that only 2 levels of categories will be displayed in the theme and be accessible to view from the main page. If you want to add deeper categories, its recommended to use the â€œCategoriesâ€ widget (watch how below).</p>

<h3 id="import-categories">Import Categories</h3>

<p>Go to <strong>Panel</strong> -&gt; <strong>Classifieds</strong> -&gt; <strong>Categories</strong>, select â€œImportâ€ and choose your csv file (<a href="https://docs.google.com/uc?id=0B60e9iwQucDwTm1NRGlqcEZwdGM&amp;export=download">example</a>). More information <a href="http://docs.yclas.com/use-import-tool-categories-locations/#import-categories">here</a>.</p>

<h2 id="how-to-manage-categories">How to manage categories</h2>

<p>Managing categories is veryÂ easy. Go to <strong>Panel</strong>, choose <strong>Classifieds</strong>Â -&gt;Â <strong>Categories</strong> on the left sidebar.</p>

<h3 id="movechange-order">Move/Change order</h3>

<p>If you want to move categories and change their order you just need to drag and drop the selected category to the place you have chosen.</p>

<h3 id="edit">Edit</h3>

<p>To change something, e.g. the name or description of the category, you can click the <strong>Edit</strong> button.</p>

<h3 id="delete">Delete</h3>

<p>To delete a category, press the red button with a trash bin. Note that when you delete the parent category, subcategories within it will be moved a level up - to become the parent of the deleted category.</p>

<h2 id="categories-widget">Categories widget</h2>

<p>The category widget gives you additional options.Â To activate it go to <strong>Panel</strong> and choose <strong>Appearance &gt;</strong>Â <strong>Widgets</strong> on the left sidebar.Â Choose <strong>â€˜Categoriesâ€™ widget</strong>Â Â from the list and click <strong>Create</strong>. Give a name to the widgetâ€™s title and choose if you want to display it in a sidebar or in the footer. You may also keep it <strong>Inactive</strong>.Â Thanks to this widget, navigation between categories is easier. A list of categories will be displayed at all times at the side or at the bottom of the page.</p>

